{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos236.erdos_236 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos236.erdos_236.","id":"vf_aec4a3e459ac99ae","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #236: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $f(n)$ count the number of solutions to $n=p+2^k$ for prime $p$ and $k\\geq 0$. Is it true that $f(n)=o(\\log n)$? Current best: Mientka and Weitzenkamp \\cite{MiWe69} have proved there are no other such $n\\leq 2^{44}$. Vaughan \\cite{Va73} has proved that the number of $n\\leq N$ such that $n-2^k$ is prime for all $2^k<n$ is\\[< \\exp\\left(-c\\frac{\\log \\log \\log N}{\\log\\log N}\\log N\\right)N\\]for some constant $c>0$. Prize: no. OEIS: A039669, A109925. Tags: number theory, primes.","id":"vf_ea088f13ed98d3c2","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/236.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_aec4a3e459ac99ae","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:236","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_aec4a3e459ac99ae","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_ea088f13ed98d3c2","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_ea088f13ed98d3c2","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:236","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier